        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 14 at 5:02PM EDT by NWS Raleigh NC</headline>
        <description>At 501 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms with
very heavy rainfall over a good portion of Nash, Halifax,
and Edgecombe Counties, moving northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Roanoke Rapids, Tarboro, Halifax, Scotland Neck, Enfield, Weldon,
Whitakers, Hobgood, Speed, and Leggett.
</description>
        <instruction>Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
